I think, as moms we can get overwhelmed with trying to make everything Pinterest-perfect for our families. And while there is nothing wrong with wanting everything a certain way, it’s also nice to remember that we can make memories with our kids by doing the simplest of things.

Here are Simple Holiday Traditions that I love: ⬇️

@crystalmendez.co 👈(follow and save this post!) Read this post online here: https://lovemoreliveblessed.com/family-christmas-traditions/

🎄 Elf on the Shelf - but keep it simple. Our elf, Chester, isn’t getting into crazy shenanigans all month long. HE JUST MOVES. That’s it. He magically moves from one spot to another. (And he might bring snacks 1 day .) 

🎄 Hot cocoa bar – This is the easiest thing in the world and my kids LOVE it. I buy a container of hot chocolate and we top our cups with either whip cream or marshmallows. Nothing fancy. The kids are allowed to have hot chocolate whenever, as long as they clean up after themselves. 

🎄 Family movie night. Super simple just add in Christmas movies and maybe some hot cocoa? Blankets and comfy pjs make this even better. We like to watch The Grinch , and It’s A Wonderful Life, and The Santa Clause.

🎄 Make one homemade ornament a year. We made these salt dough ornaments last year. I LOVED seeing them this year when we decorated the tree together. 

🎄 Build a gingerbread house together. This year we’re doing Poptart gingerbread houses. 

🤗 Happy December 1st! Let your heart be light! ✨. Comment to share your favorite holiday traditions 🎁🎁🎁

💫How do I stop being so negative? 
⁣
I asked myself that same question years ago. Learning the answer to that question got me started on a journey to find out more about positivity and how to let go of negativity. 

It took me so long to stop being pessimistic! And even now I have days where I need to self-coach myself A LOT! 

And that’s okay. I’ll never be a 100% optimist all day, forever and ever. And I’m not trying to be. 

What I am doing is focusing more and more attention on being a positive person each day. Here are some tips I found along the way 

Live in the moment 

✨Constantly thinking about your past mistakes or worrying about the future causes anxiety. 

When you catch yourself judging yourself for something in your past or worrying about the future do something to make you focus on the present moment. 

✨Write yourself positivity notes

These notes can be affirmations, bible verses or quotes you love. Write in on flashcards 
or in your notes app. 

✨Stop spending time with negative people and making negative lifestyle choices.

✨Look for the positive every single day

👉🏼Journal - free write each day to get things off your mind. 

👉🏼Tell yourself 3 good things every single day

👉🏼Take a gratitude challenge every month 

Taking small steps to positivity every single day will 100% change your life! 😎

Truth - I've been told my optimism is annoying AF. I know it's annoying to have someone who is always looking on the bright side around you when you don't wanna see the silver lining. I get it. I'm not happy and optimistic 24/7. I work hard on keeping myself in the right mindset. Mindset is every fucking thing. Keeping the right mindset helps me show up for myself, for my kids and for my family. So, if my optimism is annoying to you, #sorrynotsorry. I still love you though.

Truth - "You're not doing self-care, you're being a selfish bitxh! Someone said this to me and I cried. Guess what I realized? This was all about boundaries. I set some STRICT boundaries for how I would be treated,NO MORE PEOPLE PLEASING. And these boundaries set off bombs with the people around me who kept crossing them. Setting boundaries is hard. Letting people walk all over you is hard. Choose your hard.
 
Truth - It's a little bit tough around here right now. I'm in the last (and most challenging) semester of my LVN to RN Bridge Program. My house is not as clean as I want it to be. My exercise goals are pretty much out the window. I have a running to do list in my head that’s a mile long. I made a mistake in my business account and ended up over $600 in the hole, so damn frustrating! I almost forgot to pay my mortgage. I am breaking out on my chin/neck area probably from stress. I cut my own hair (even though I said I wouldn’t anymore) and I hate it. I'm tired. And a little tiny bit of stress goes everywhere with me.
 
And still - I'm generously, excitedly optimistic. Why? Because this shit is all gonna work itself out. I know it, I feel it in my heart. I tell myself things like: I believe I am divinely guided. I believe thing will work out for me no matter what. I believe God will make a way, even when I think there is no way. I live an abundant life. I am always taken care of. 
 
Point of this - live your life how you want it. Let yourself be realistic about your circumstances and still wake up every day with wild optimism. It will change your life! Be you and love exactly who you are. #selfcareisntselfish

It’s time for a BOOST of positivity 💥 Save these 5 easy ways to focus on optimism, and the next time you’re feeling blah read them again. 🥰

How many of these tips are you already incorporating into your daily life? 

1. Gratitude - I’m not consistent with my journaling yet but I still run through a list of gratitude in my mind every day. Most days it’s the simple things I love the most - my husbands smile, the teens chatting with me on the way to school, having hot coffee on a cold day. 

2. Surround yourself with positivity. I’m ruthless about who I follow and the stories I watch. Use that mute or unfollow button! 

3. Focus on solutions. Continuing  to get upset about the problem doesn’t fix it, looking for answers/solutions does. 

4. Be nice to yourself. How are you talking to yourself? Start with affirmations if this is hard for you. DM if you need ideas 💡 

And last but not least…

5. Do things that bring you joy. Simple things bring me so much joy like crochet 🧶 or reading. Taking a bit of time for myself on a busy day is renewing! 

Happy Friday! Let me know if these help and tell me what you’d add in the comments.

✨This is your sign to start showing up for yourself.✨ 

For a stretch of years I focused on being there for everyone except myself. I was the go-to support person, if you needed money, a babysitter, someone to listen to you vent - I was your girl. 

Often I would stop what I was doing or break promises to myself in order to meet the needs of others. 

I was a giver. And I gave and gave until there was nothing left to give. 

That left me with a ton of resentment, bad skin, no savings, and bad health because I wasn’t prioritizing myself. 

Let’s help you avoid all that! 🫵🏼

➡️3 Ways to Start Showing up for Yourself 

✨Keep your promises to yourself.  Practice holding yourself accountable. Do what you say you’re going to do. Writing down your goals helps you reach them! 

✨Forgive yourself. Compassion and love is not reserved for how you treat others. You deserve compassion and love from yourself too. 

✨Commit to your health. This can be overwhelming. I suggest picking 1 good habit to add into your life, once you got that habit integrated add the next thing. Take your vitamins, stay hydrated and move your body. And most importantly - take time for REST!

I didn’t grow up with role models who took care of themselves. Most often the women in my life gave so much of themselves and got burned out so many times. 

I grew to be that woman, mom, friend. You could count on me for cash, babysitting, hanging out even when I didn’t want to, or needed to prioritize myself. 

Most of the time I was anxious and didn’t realize it. I was busy sticking my nose into shit that was none of my business and I was burned out and resentful of always being the one available to help but not getting that help back in return. 

I’m Feb of 2019 (2/24/19) I found @hiatusspa and read about their spa subscription program. 

I didn’t feel like I deserved such a luxury but I went out of my comfort zone and signed up! 

Prioritizing my self- my body, my mind has been such a breakthrough for me. I wish my mom, tias and grandma would have been able to do this for themselves. I wish I could have watched them relax in a healthy way and show me this was possible. 

Now I am celebrating 🥳 4 years with @hiatusspa which is 4 years of saying Crystal you are more than worthy! Crystal you deserve to rest. Crystal you can splurge on yourself. 

My spa days are one part of my self- care not the whole thing. I wanna encourage you - if you haven’t been prioritizing yourself PLEASE START NOW! 

You are more than worthy. You are deserving. You can rest. ❤️

🚨 How to Really Make Changes in Your Life🚨

🤩 If you’re wondering where to start to introduce positive habits into your life, save this reel. 

The firs step is to make taking care of yourself, putting yourself first - NORMAL. This is hard for us moms, I know! But, it’s necessary and possible. 

Start small. 

Are you sleeping enough?

Can you add more water into your day? 

What kind of media are you consuming? Start unfollowing people/pages that don’t make you feel good. Be mindful of the stories you watch. 

Who are you spending the most time with? How do you feel around them? Do your friendships and relationships have reciprocity? Are you always the giver? Who can you reach out to for help? 

Move your body. You can keep it simple and just walk daily. Move your body to benefit your overall health not just for weight loss reasons. I ignored the high blood pressure readings for a year before I finally did anything about them (that’s a whole other story!) 

Start a hobby just for fun. 

It’s not easy to do self-care and put yourself first right away. Is it worth it? Yes. Is it life-changing? Yes. Can you do it? Yes, I believe in you. You got this!

🚨Negative thoughts are not always a bad thing!!🚨 

I love to look on the positive side, and being wildly optimistic has served me well. Today though -lets talk about negativity because it’s not always a bad thing…

➡️ Negative thoughts can help you see things more realistically. Sometimes it makes sense to be realistic of what is going on in your life rather than wildly optimistic. For example- in my own life - quitting the highest paying corporate job I had because the expectations were crazy  and work/life balance was non-existent. I tried staying on (focusing on positivity as much as possible) until I took a realistic look at how I felt and realized NOPE this ain’t’ the place for me. 

➡️ Negative thoughts aren’t always a bad thing! Don’t beat yourself up for having them! Just like in the above example, negative thoughts can help you see a situation/relationship/person for what it truly is. And those thoughts can help you form a positive way into how you want to move into the future. 

➡️ The human brain has a natural tendency to remember negative experiences/interactions more than positive. Have you noticed this? It’s not just YOU! I promise, it’s all of us! 

Save this post to refer back to it when you feel like you’re the only negative person around. I promise you’re not!

Are you letting all the little things bother you? Try these five tips. 

1. Focus on the big picture. Make sure you put your energy somewhere else rather than berating yourself for this small mistake. Don’t forget to give your spouse and kids the benefit of the doubt too. You don’t want to make them feel terrible over things that won’t matter in 5 hours, much less 5 days from now. 

2.  You can learn from mistakes. Instead of letting things destroy your attitude and positive outlook, challenge yourself to find the bright side of the situation or a learning point. Don’t let one bad moment ruin your day or your progress. 

3. Forgive others. By choosing empathy over anger you can create calm in a stressful situation. 

4. Know when to let go. If you have a hard time forgiving yourself, try this: if a friend came to you saying they committed this same mistake what advice would you give them? How would you treat them? 

5. Don’t worry about what other people think about you. Do NOT make your life decisions based on what you believe people think about you. When you let go of the power of other people’s opinions in your life is when you truly stop letting the little things bother you. 

Save this reel to reference the next time you’re feeling bothered!

This is my why….

As a mom and step-mom to three kids, wife, daughter, sister and nurse, I absolutely made ZERO time for taking care of myself. Even thinking about visiting a spa, getting a massage or going out of town by myself made me feel so damn guilty. 

At this point in my life I was 29 years old, overweight, bad skin, crazy looking clothes. I was also a people pleaser and could not, would not say to NO to anyone. Have you ever been a people pleaser? How about having trouble with boundaries and letting people walk all over you? Yeah, that was me too. 

In 2018 I started taking self-care seriously. I bought a spa subscription (yes, it’s soooo worth it and cheaper than you may think) and started to make some major changes in my life: 

➡️Set boundaries with my family (this was uncomfortable and took years) 
Set boundaries with my friends 

➡️Let go of friendships/relationships that no longer worked/were too negative/draining 

➡️Learned how to let go of mom guilt 

➡️Made self-care a part of everyday life

Want to know the best result of all this? Realizing my worth and value as a person. 

Falling in love with who I am and learning to love my body and have enough courage to make changes and not care what other people think.

My blog, Love More Live Blessed, morphed from constantly searching for love and trying to find out how to be the best person into learning that living my best life meant LOVING MYSELF MORE.

Love really does change everything.

If you get anything from  reading this today, get this: you have to love yourself more.

This quest towards positivity and self-care and self-love has been one of the most rewarding journeys in life. I’m happy you’re here to be part of it and hope I can add some positivity into your journey too!

Why your affirmations aren’t working. ⬇️🤯

You don’t believe them. You don’t believe these affirmations could be true. You’re not feeling the emotions that live along side with an affirmation like “I am loved, adored, cared for.”

As a mom and step-mom to three kids, wife, daughter, sister and nurse, I absolutely made ZERO time for taking care of myself. Even thinking about visiting a spa, getting a massage or going out of town by myself made me feel so damn guilty.

At this point in my life I was 29 years old, overweight, bad skin, crazy looking clothes. I was also a people pleaser and could not, would not say to NO to anyone. In 2018 I started taking self-care seriously. I bought a spa subscription (yes, it’s soooo worth it and cheaper than you may think) and started to make some major changes in my life:

➡️Set boundaries with my family (this was uncomfortable and took years)
Set boundaries with my friends

➡️Let go of friendships/relationships that no longer worked/were too negative/draining

➡️Learned how to let go of mom guilt

➡️Made self-care a part of everyday life

Want to know the best result of all this? Realizing my worth and value as a person.

Falling in love with who I am and learning to love my body and have enough courage to make changes and not care what other people think.

My blog, Love More Live Blessed, morphed from constantly searching for love and trying to find out how to be the best person into learning that living my best life meant LOVING MYSELF MORE.

Love really does change everything.

If you get anything from reading this today, get this: you have to love yourself more.

This quest towards positivity and self-care and self-love has been one of the most rewarding journeys in life. I’m happy you’re here to be part of it and hope I can add some positivity into your journey too!

-Let’s shift our perspective on handling life’s frustrations. Yes, there will always be moments that test our patience or trigger annoyance. It’s a natural part of life. However, choosing to stay focused in those negative feelings is just that - a choice. By consciously redirecting our focus towards the positives, even in challenging situations, you’ll notice a remarkable transformation in your mindset. Embracing optimism isn’t ignoring the negatives; it’s choosing to rise above them.

-Let’s shift away from limited thinking and start embracing a broader vision. Instead of asking, “What could go wrong?” let’s begin to wonder, “How could this go right?” Remember, every action begins as a thought, whether it’s a positive or negative one. Be mindful of the ideas you nurture in your mind, as they are the seeds that grow into the events of your life. 
-

-Sometimes, the most powerful response is to observe, reflect, and choose silence or inaction, especially if reacting does not serve our higher purpose or well-being.

So, in your journey, consider each moment carefully. Decide if a reaction aligns with your goals, values, and the person you aspire to be. 

Often, the strength lies in choosing not to engage, preserving your energy for what truly enriches your life.

Unpopular opinion 👋

Letting go of friendships that no longer serve you is not just okay, it’s often necessary for your personal growth and well-being. 

Here’s why:
Growth and Change: As we evolve, our needs, interests, and values can shift. Friendships based on past versions of ourselves may not fit who we are today. It’s natural and healthy to outgrow certain relationships as you grow into your true self.

Energy and Well-being: Your energy and well-being should be a priority. If a friendship is consistently draining, negative, or unsupportive, it’s taking valuable energy away from your own health and other positive relationships in your life.

Reciprocity and Balance: Healthy relationships are based on mutual respect and reciprocity. If you find yourself in a one-sided friendship where your efforts aren’t reciprocated, it’s a signal that the relationship isn’t balanced and might not be beneficial for you.

Space for New Connections: Letting go of friendships that no longer serve you creates space for new, more fulfilling relationships. It opens you up to connect with people who align more closely with your current path and values.

Self-Respect: Choosing to step away from friendships that aren’t serving you is a powerful act of self-respect. It shows that you value yourself enough to make choices that positively impact your life.

Quality Over Quantity: It’s the quality of friendships, not the quantity, that truly enriches your life. Investing in fewer, more meaningful relationships can be far more rewarding than maintaining numerous unfulfilling connections.

Life’s Seasons: Just like seasons, friendships can have a natural lifespan. Some are meant to last a lifetime, others for a specific chapter. Recognizing and accepting the seasonal nature of certain friendships can bring a sense of peace and closure.

Remember, it’s important to let go with kindness and respect, both for yourself and the other person involved. Transitioning away from a friendship doesn’t have to be dramatic; it can be a gentle and gradual process. 
Trust your instincts, under your needs, and know that it’s OK to prioritize your journey and well-being.
